  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T044-03 by repairing `CitationExtractor.NormalizeStatute` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs`. The normalizer concatenates the regex section
    capture verbatim (including subsection parentheticals), yielding `17 U.S.C. § 512(c)(1)(A)` instead of the canonical `17 U.S.C. § 512`.

    Production fix per ledger Recommended Fix section: strip the parenthetical in the normalizer:

    ```
    var section = m.Groups["section"].Value.Trim();
    var parenStart = section.IndexOf('(');
    if (parenStart >= 0) section = section[..parenStart];
    return $"{title} U.S.C. § {section}";
    ```

    Test impact: 1 Skip'd test (`ExtractCitations_Statute_StripsSubsectionsInNormalizedKey` Fact) flips Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T044-03" + resolution mode `repaired`.

    Coordination: `CitationExtractor.cs` is SHARED with task 033 (RB-T044-05 RegulationPattern). Task 033 is marked
    `parallel-safe: false` and waits for THIS task to land first.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs` `NormalizeStatute` truncates the section capture at the first
    `(` before concatenating. 1 Skip'd test in the corresponding test file passes when re-enabled. Ledger row RB-T044-03 status → `repaired`.

    Existing passing Statute Theory cases continue to pass (no regression on canonical `§ 101`-style cites).
  </goal>

