  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T044-03 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-07-31): the regex captures `(?<section>\d[\d\-\.]*[a-z]?(?:\([a-z0-9]+\))*)` including subsection parentheticals; the bug is only in the NORMALIZER (canonical key), not the regex itself. Per Phase 2 work, tasks 020 (RB-T044-02 NormalizeCaseLaw) and 021 (RB-T044-04 NormalizePatent) already touched this file. Phase 2 is COMPLETE before Phase 3 starts (Phase 1/2/3 are strictly sequential at phase boundaries), so no parallelism risk with those Phase 2 tasks.

      Within Phase 3: task 033 (RB-T044-05 RegulationPattern) ALSO touches this file. Task 033 is marked `parallel-safe: false` and serialized after this task.
    </background>
