  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load r1 ledger entry RB-T044-03 (lines ~325-358) for documented bug + recommended fix.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs` focusing on `NormalizeStatute(Match m)` (~line 172).</step>
    <step order="3">Implement the fix: extract `section` from `m.Groups["section"].Value.Trim()`; truncate at first `(`; concatenate. Preserve method signature and return shape.</step>
    <step order="4">Build BFF: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Zero new warnings.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractorTests.cs`: remove `Skip = "..."` on `ExtractCitations_Statute_StripsSubsectionsInNormalizedKey`; remove per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` override.</step>
    <step order="6">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~CitationExtractorTests"`. Re-enabled test must pass; existing Statute Theory cases must still pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` RB-T044-03 row: status → `repaired`, fix-commit SHA placeholder + today's date.</step>
    <step order="8">Commit: `fix(bff-api): trim subsection parenthetical in NormalizeStatute (RB-T044-03; repaired)` — message cites entry ID + resolution mode per NFR-04.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion + commit SHA. Flag that task 033 may now proceed (file conflict cleared).</step>
  </steps>

